WEBVTT

00:03.742 --> 00:04.091
.

00:04.134 --> 00:06.049
- Previously on
"Midnight, Texas"...

00:06.093 --> 00:07.094
- Your father hired me.

00:07.137 --> 00:08.660
- Do you know why my dad

00:08.704 --> 00:10.010
is having me followed?

00:10.053 --> 00:12.055
- We need more lime.
- Ow.

00:12.099 --> 00:13.448
- Oh, my God.
I'm so sorry.

00:17.060 --> 00:18.670
- Kai's a very good man.

00:18.714 --> 00:21.412
That trip was supposed to be
a romantic getaway,

00:21.456 --> 00:24.198
but instead, he took
Lyric and Sequoia.

00:24.241 --> 00:26.635
- Well, no relationship
is perfect, huh?

00:26.678 --> 00:28.506
- I found out there's
a curse on my family.

00:28.550 --> 00:31.031
Anyone I find real love
with dies.

00:31.074 --> 00:32.075
I'm so sorry, Bobo.

00:32.119 --> 00:33.294
It's only until I figure out

00:33.337 --> 00:34.817
what to do about this curse.

00:34.860 --> 00:37.211
- I see you found
Kai's ancestor.

00:37.254 --> 00:39.300
It's where Kai gets all of his
juju from.

00:39.343 --> 00:41.302
Do you ever wish Lem
wasn't a vampire?

00:41.345 --> 00:43.391
- In my previous life,
I wanted kids.

00:43.434 --> 00:46.698
But having a child may be
a way of healing the past.

00:47.612 --> 00:52.661
- ♪ All I want is a stocking
with my name on it ♪

00:52.704 --> 00:54.445
♪

00:54.489 --> 00:56.317
♪ Hanging next to a stocking
with your name on it ♪

00:56.360 --> 00:59.972
- [gasps]
She just kicked.

01:00.016 --> 01:01.235
- A girl?

01:01.278 --> 01:03.585
- Oh, yeah.

01:03.628 --> 01:05.456
You're outnumbered.

01:05.500 --> 01:08.329
- Well...

01:08.372 --> 01:11.288
I'm okay with that.

01:11.332 --> 01:14.900
- ♪ Carried away

01:14.944 --> 01:16.380
- Hey, Lem.

01:16.424 --> 01:18.774
Lem.
Lem.

01:20.906 --> 01:23.083
Looks like you need a refill.

01:23.126 --> 01:24.736
- It's Olivia.

01:24.780 --> 01:26.695
My psychic connection
is getting stronger.

01:26.738 --> 01:28.740
I just saw her dreams
for the first time,

01:28.784 --> 01:31.569
and it was--
- Scary?

01:31.613 --> 01:32.570
Sexy?

01:32.614 --> 01:33.702
♪

01:33.745 --> 01:34.877
Both?

01:34.920 --> 01:37.445
- It was something I could
never give her.

01:38.185 --> 01:41.405
[solemn music]

01:49.196 --> 01:50.893
- [exhales deeply]

01:52.721 --> 01:54.288
[sighs]

02:05.037 --> 02:06.865
Lem, what are you doing?

02:06.909 --> 02:08.040
No!

02:08.084 --> 02:11.000
[dramatic music]

02:11.043 --> 02:12.610
Lem?

02:12.654 --> 02:19.704
♪

02:20.009 --> 02:21.619
- Good morning.

02:24.927 --> 02:27.886
[dramatic music]

02:27.930 --> 02:30.150
♪

02:32.108 --> 02:33.979
- You're human now

02:34.023 --> 02:37.635
because I had a weird dream?

02:37.679 --> 02:39.942
- I could feel your desire
for a child.

02:39.985 --> 02:42.640
Something I could never
give you as a vampire.

02:42.684 --> 02:45.948
But then I realized that
with Kai, there was a way.

02:45.991 --> 02:48.124
- Are you sure you're
ready for this?

02:48.168 --> 02:50.344
To be human again?
To be mortal?

02:50.387 --> 02:52.041
It's a big change.

02:52.084 --> 02:53.912
- Yes, I'm ready.

02:53.956 --> 02:55.566
[intense music]

02:55.610 --> 02:57.264
- [gasps]

02:57.307 --> 03:00.963
♪

03:01.006 --> 03:02.530
- How could you make
a decision like this

03:02.573 --> 03:03.879
without talking to me first?

03:03.922 --> 03:05.489
We are married, Lem.

03:05.533 --> 03:08.318
We're supposed to make
decisions together, remember?

03:08.362 --> 03:09.972
- 'Cause I knew you'd say "no."

03:10.015 --> 03:11.843
- Of course, I'd say "no."

03:13.280 --> 03:16.500
Lem, we work because
you're a vampire

03:16.544 --> 03:19.329
and I am a really
messed up human.

03:19.373 --> 03:23.464
- We work because we love
each other.

03:23.507 --> 03:26.162
[soft music]

03:26.206 --> 03:29.034
After Mary, I knew you
wanted a family.

03:29.078 --> 03:31.689
Now I want that too.

03:31.733 --> 03:33.691
♪

03:33.735 --> 03:36.825
- [sighs]
- I want everything with you.

03:36.868 --> 03:38.566
♪

03:39.958 --> 03:42.134
- Good morning.

03:42.178 --> 03:43.223
Hmm.

03:43.266 --> 03:46.487
[cell phone buzzing]

03:50.230 --> 03:53.145
Well, there goes my happy.

03:53.189 --> 03:55.452
- Kai?

03:55.496 --> 03:59.630
- Yeah, he--uh,
he and the girls are back.

04:01.545 --> 04:03.330
- If you're unhappy,
why do you stay with him?

04:03.373 --> 04:05.419
- Kai and I have been together
for a long time.

04:05.462 --> 04:08.030
We help a lot of people
through our work.

04:08.073 --> 04:11.816
And sometimes when your life
is so entwined with someone's

04:11.860 --> 04:15.907
sometimes it's easier
to just stay stuck

04:15.951 --> 04:17.561
- I get it.

04:17.605 --> 04:19.041
I think.

04:19.084 --> 04:20.912
- But that does not mean

04:20.956 --> 04:23.350
that I want this to end.

04:26.091 --> 04:29.269
[Tommy James and the
Shondells'"Draggin' the Line"]

04:29.312 --> 04:32.924
♪

04:32.968 --> 04:34.274
- Excuse me.

04:34.317 --> 04:36.276
Get that dog
out of my restaurant, Fiji.

04:36.319 --> 04:37.886
- This is not a dog, it's Bobo.

04:37.929 --> 04:38.756
[dog barks]

04:38.800 --> 04:40.105
- And he's staying with me.

04:40.149 --> 04:42.107
- You--you know what?

04:42.151 --> 04:43.587
- Hmm?

04:43.631 --> 04:45.763
- I don't wanna know.

04:45.807 --> 04:47.983
♪

04:48.026 --> 04:50.333
- I'm guessing this
is curse-related?

04:50.377 --> 04:52.553
- I really want to pet him,

04:52.596 --> 04:54.424
but it feels wrong, right?

04:54.468 --> 04:56.165
- I think it's fine.

04:56.208 --> 04:58.341
I'm just desperate.

04:58.385 --> 05:01.344
Bobo's safe as a dog,
but it's temporary.

05:01.388 --> 05:03.215
I mean, I've tried everything.

05:03.259 --> 05:06.306
But, eventually,
the curse always wins.

05:06.349 --> 05:08.743
- We can help.
We'll find something.

05:08.786 --> 05:09.874
- You can't.

05:09.918 --> 05:11.876
This has something to do
with my lineage.

05:11.920 --> 05:14.662
And the problem is,
my books are useless

05:14.705 --> 05:17.665
when I have no idea what
this curse is even about.

05:17.708 --> 05:19.144
- Maybe another witch
could help?

05:19.188 --> 05:20.450
- Well, it is a family curse.

05:20.494 --> 05:22.322
You got any other
witchy relatives?

05:22.365 --> 05:23.627
- Not that I know of.

05:23.671 --> 05:25.150
- You know, back in
the Salem days,

05:25.194 --> 05:27.152
there was an underground
witch network, where witches

05:27.196 --> 05:28.850
could share knowledge
without being discovered.

05:28.893 --> 05:31.940
Maybe something like that
still exists today?

05:31.983 --> 05:36.118
- ♪ I'm talking 'bout
peace of mind ♪

05:36.161 --> 05:37.772
- I could probably look into...

05:37.815 --> 05:40.383
- ♪ Take my time

05:40.427 --> 05:43.517
♪ I'm getting the good sign

05:43.560 --> 05:45.301
♪

05:45.345 --> 05:47.825
♪ Draggin' the line,
draggin' the line ♪

05:47.869 --> 05:49.566
♪

05:49.610 --> 05:50.828
♪ Draggin' the line

05:50.872 --> 05:51.873
- What's going on?

05:51.916 --> 05:53.657
- I went to see Kai last night.

05:53.701 --> 05:56.138
- Goddess give me strength.

05:56.181 --> 05:58.227
- First the Rev and now you?

05:58.270 --> 05:59.837
What the hell is happening?

05:59.881 --> 06:01.709
- Well, I am happy
for you, man.

06:01.752 --> 06:03.711
Must be amazing to stand
in the sunlight

06:03.754 --> 06:05.103
after all these years.

06:05.147 --> 06:07.845
- Yeah, I became a vampire
to gain freedom,

06:07.889 --> 06:10.413
and it was a prison
in its own way.

06:10.457 --> 06:11.849
- You don't feel vulnerable?

06:11.893 --> 06:14.417
- Why would you give up
your power just like that?

06:17.115 --> 06:19.727
- Sometimes there are
more important things.

06:22.556 --> 06:25.428
Madonna, could I please have

06:25.472 --> 06:27.865
a strawberry milkshake

06:27.909 --> 06:31.391
with whipped cream
and a cherry?

06:31.434 --> 06:33.523
[dramatic music]

06:33.567 --> 06:36.744
I've been wanting to try this
since the '50s.

06:39.747 --> 06:41.052
- This is interesting.

06:41.096 --> 06:45.056
"The Delilahs:
Witches Helping Witches."

06:45.100 --> 06:46.884
This does look like
the right place.

06:46.928 --> 06:49.147
Submit post.

06:49.191 --> 06:51.585
"Need help.

06:51.628 --> 06:54.718
"My family was cursed
by Dark Witches,

06:54.762 --> 06:58.113
"and now my true love
is destined

06:58.156 --> 07:00.637
"to die a violent death.

07:00.681 --> 07:04.685
How do I stop it?
Help."

07:05.512 --> 07:08.079
[dramatic music]

07:08.123 --> 07:09.994
"You don't belong here."

07:10.038 --> 07:12.562
♪

07:12.606 --> 07:14.085
They kicked me out.

07:14.129 --> 07:17.262
I thought women were
supposed to help each other.

07:17.306 --> 07:18.481
[sighs]

07:18.525 --> 07:20.352
You got any bright ideas?

07:20.396 --> 07:24.008
♪

07:26.010 --> 07:27.925
[device beeping]

07:29.536 --> 07:32.495
[suspenseful music]

07:32.539 --> 07:39.763
♪

07:56.824 --> 08:00.480
- Honey, I am home.

08:03.004 --> 08:04.484
- The mall?

08:04.527 --> 08:06.311
Definitely human.

08:06.355 --> 08:08.575
- Yeah, I went a little crazy.

08:08.618 --> 08:10.707
But there was a sale so...

08:10.751 --> 08:14.319
- I didn't know I was pregnant.

08:14.363 --> 08:16.147
- Not now, but soon.

08:16.191 --> 08:18.541
You know, I was thinking
I could build us a house.

08:18.585 --> 08:20.325
There's a lot for sale
down the road.

08:20.369 --> 08:23.415
- Okay just--stop.

08:23.459 --> 08:24.808
- I thought this was
what you wanted.

08:24.852 --> 08:26.897
- Uh, actually, it's not.

08:26.941 --> 08:30.510
Lem, it was easy
to fantasize

08:30.553 --> 08:32.294
about having
a family together,

08:32.337 --> 08:34.731
because up until last night,

08:34.775 --> 08:36.124
it was impossible.

08:36.167 --> 08:37.821
- But now it is possible.

08:37.865 --> 08:39.693
- Except you know my childhood

08:39.736 --> 08:42.609
wasn't exactly pool parties
and Sunday suppers.

08:42.652 --> 08:45.350
- But that doesn't mean you
can't be a great parent.

08:45.394 --> 08:47.004
- [scoffs]

08:47.048 --> 08:49.050
Doesn't it?

08:49.093 --> 08:51.792
♪

08:51.835 --> 08:54.664
My mom got sick
and died when I was nine.

08:54.708 --> 08:57.362
My father abandoned me
with an evil stepmother.

08:57.406 --> 08:59.930
♪

08:59.974 --> 09:02.106
What the hell do I know
about family?

09:02.150 --> 09:03.586
- You rarely talk about
your mother.

09:03.630 --> 09:06.894
- Because...
[sighs]

09:06.937 --> 09:08.460
I can't.

09:08.504 --> 09:11.376
I can't be a mom.

09:11.420 --> 09:13.857
I can't...

09:13.901 --> 09:16.730
Show a child what love
looks like.

09:16.773 --> 09:17.905
- That's not true.

09:17.948 --> 09:20.385
- You may be human now...

09:20.429 --> 09:22.692
♪

09:22.736 --> 09:25.390
But I am still broken.

09:25.434 --> 09:27.915
- [moaning]

09:27.958 --> 09:29.656
- Are you sure we should
be doing this in the hotel?

09:29.699 --> 09:30.918
- Oh, Kai's meditating.

09:30.961 --> 09:32.572
He won't even notice
we're gone.

09:32.615 --> 09:35.836
[moaning]

09:36.532 --> 09:38.142
[woman screams]

09:38.186 --> 09:40.231
[dramatic music]

09:40.275 --> 09:41.493
- [gasps]

09:41.537 --> 09:43.626
Sequoia.

09:43.670 --> 09:45.802
What happened?

09:45.846 --> 09:47.456
♪

09:47.499 --> 09:49.589
Oh, my...
[sobbing]

09:49.632 --> 09:50.764
- I tried to save her.

09:50.807 --> 09:52.635
She's gone.

09:52.679 --> 09:55.246
- [whimpering]

09:55.290 --> 09:58.423
♪

09:58.467 --> 10:00.730
[sobbing]

10:00.774 --> 10:02.645
♪

10:06.562 --> 10:06.736
.

10:06.780 --> 10:08.042
- [sobbing]

10:08.085 --> 10:09.217
- Did you have any idea

10:09.260 --> 10:11.872
she was depressed,
suicidal?

10:11.915 --> 10:14.657
- Well, obviously not,
or I would have helped her.

10:14.701 --> 10:15.876
That's what I do.

10:15.919 --> 10:17.921
- This is hard on all of us.

10:17.965 --> 10:20.968
- [weeping]

10:21.011 --> 10:22.273
- Oh, poor Lyric.

10:22.317 --> 10:24.362
They were like sisters.

10:24.406 --> 10:26.103
I'll get her something
to calm down

10:26.147 --> 10:27.670
while we wait
for the paramedics.

10:27.714 --> 10:31.413
- I don't--I don't understand
why she'd do this.

10:31.456 --> 10:33.415
She had her whole life
ahead of her.

10:33.458 --> 10:35.896
- Well, maybe she
can tell us.

10:35.939 --> 10:40.074
♪

10:40.117 --> 10:42.903
[whooshing]

10:42.946 --> 10:45.906
[suspenseful music]

10:45.949 --> 10:49.561
♪

10:49.605 --> 10:51.651
- Anything?

10:51.694 --> 10:53.304
- No.

10:53.348 --> 10:54.915
No, she's not here.

10:54.958 --> 11:01.878
♪

11:07.710 --> 11:09.190
[breathing heavily]

11:09.233 --> 11:10.800
What was that all about?

11:10.844 --> 11:13.107
♪

11:13.150 --> 11:14.674
Who cut your tongue out?

11:14.717 --> 11:16.458
Kai.

11:16.501 --> 11:18.678
[gasping]

11:26.250 --> 11:29.210
[soft oldies music]

11:29.253 --> 11:36.521
♪

11:37.609 --> 11:38.698
[thud]

11:38.741 --> 11:39.481
[grunts]

11:39.524 --> 11:42.310
[heartbeat thudding]

11:42.353 --> 11:44.399
[heavy breathing]

11:44.442 --> 11:47.054
♪

11:47.097 --> 11:50.361
[wheezing]

11:53.277 --> 11:54.888
No.

11:54.931 --> 11:57.151
[breathing heavily]

11:57.194 --> 11:59.806
What the hell was that?

12:00.850 --> 12:02.156
- He gave up immortality

12:02.199 --> 12:03.548
to make your dreams
come true.

12:03.592 --> 12:04.767
- Hmm.

12:04.811 --> 12:07.204
- That's pretty romantic,
if you ask me.

12:09.380 --> 12:11.556
It is.
And I'm gonna go lock up, okay?

12:11.600 --> 12:13.167
- Okay.

12:13.210 --> 12:15.038
I'm gonna top off.

12:15.082 --> 12:16.170
[cell phone buzzes]

12:16.213 --> 12:18.650
Oh.

12:18.694 --> 12:21.131
Madonna, your phone
is ringing.

12:21.175 --> 12:24.004
"Charity Security?"

12:24.047 --> 12:27.007
[dramatic music]

12:27.050 --> 12:34.318
♪

12:35.406 --> 12:37.800
How long have you been
working for my father?

12:37.844 --> 12:39.454
- Olivia...

12:39.497 --> 12:41.369
I can explain.

12:41.412 --> 12:44.067
- I'm done talking.

12:44.111 --> 12:47.375
[groaning]

12:50.770 --> 12:53.903
[Republica's "Ready to Go"]

12:53.947 --> 12:55.513
- Who the hell are you?

12:55.557 --> 12:56.993
- Real name's Simone Davis.

12:57.037 --> 12:59.213
I enlisted when I was 18.

12:59.256 --> 13:01.041
I dreamed of being
Special Ops--

13:01.084 --> 13:02.956
- [grunts]

13:02.999 --> 13:05.915
[grunting]

13:05.959 --> 13:09.005
[cracking]

13:10.093 --> 13:11.573
Land mine ended my career.

13:11.616 --> 13:12.748
That's when things got dark.

13:12.792 --> 13:13.836
- [grunts]

13:13.880 --> 13:15.185
♪

13:15.229 --> 13:16.752
- Your father heard my story.

13:16.796 --> 13:18.058
[grunting]

13:18.101 --> 13:20.930
Offered me a job
at Charity Private Securities,

13:20.974 --> 13:24.673
a new lease on life.

13:24.716 --> 13:28.329
- ♪ Baby, I'm ready to go

13:28.372 --> 13:30.070
♪ Baby, I'm ready to go

13:30.113 --> 13:31.767
- [groans]

13:31.811 --> 13:32.899
- Why'd he hire you?

13:32.942 --> 13:34.770
- [gasps]

13:34.814 --> 13:37.860
It was just surveillance
at first,

13:37.904 --> 13:40.080
but it escalated.

13:40.123 --> 13:42.082
He wanted your blood.

13:42.125 --> 13:44.736
- My blood?

13:44.780 --> 13:45.607
Why?

13:45.650 --> 13:47.130
- You can ask him yourself.

13:47.174 --> 13:48.566
Here.

13:48.610 --> 13:50.264
The address is in there.

13:50.307 --> 13:51.743
He's close.

13:51.787 --> 13:53.267
Look, it was just a job
at first.

13:53.310 --> 13:56.009
I didn't know that I was
gonna fall in love

13:56.052 --> 13:57.880
with this crazy-ass town.

13:57.924 --> 13:59.403
- I trusted you.

13:59.447 --> 14:01.101
- I'm sorry.

14:01.144 --> 14:04.017
- If I ever see you again,

14:04.060 --> 14:05.453
I will kill you.

14:05.496 --> 14:08.456
[dramatic music]

14:08.499 --> 14:10.806
♪

14:10.850 --> 14:12.939
[dog barking]

14:12.982 --> 14:15.376
- My Goddess, Bobo.

14:15.419 --> 14:18.335
Cut it out.

14:18.379 --> 14:19.902
- Oh, hi, sweetie.

14:19.946 --> 14:21.948
I hope you don't mind,
I let myself in.

14:21.991 --> 14:24.733
I was getting dirt
on my Chanels.

14:24.776 --> 14:26.343
- Uh...

14:26.387 --> 14:28.519
- Oh, that's enough of that,
Lassie.

14:28.563 --> 14:30.826
[barking muted]

14:30.870 --> 14:32.132
- You're a witch.

14:32.175 --> 14:33.916
Who are you?

14:33.960 --> 14:35.962
- Put the pistols down,
cowgirl.

14:36.005 --> 14:39.661
I keep tabs on the
"Witches Helping Witches" site,

14:39.704 --> 14:42.664
always on the lookout
for sisters like you.

14:43.883 --> 14:45.362
I'm Celeste.

14:45.406 --> 14:46.494
Hi.

14:46.537 --> 14:49.105
- Hi, oh.
- Mwah. Mwah.

14:50.759 --> 14:52.543
- Well, they kicked me
off the site.

14:52.587 --> 14:54.284
They were so rude.

14:54.328 --> 14:55.329
- That's the Delilahs.

14:55.372 --> 14:56.591
They think that we're catty,

14:56.634 --> 14:59.072
but they're the real bitches.

14:59.115 --> 15:01.683
- Wait, who are the Delilahs?

15:01.726 --> 15:03.946
- No one's taught you
your witch history?

15:03.990 --> 15:06.993
Wow, you really do live
in flyover country.

15:07.036 --> 15:09.169
- Sorry, did you just
come here to insult me?

15:09.212 --> 15:10.692
- No,

15:10.735 --> 15:13.956
I came because I know what
you're going through.

15:14.000 --> 15:15.175
I'm cursed too.

15:15.218 --> 15:16.959
- But it's a family curse.

15:17.003 --> 15:18.874
I don't know you.

15:18.918 --> 15:22.008
- Sit, please.

15:22.051 --> 15:25.707
All witches are descended
from an original witch.

15:25.750 --> 15:29.363
Delilah--the "good witches,"

15:29.406 --> 15:32.496
or Theophilus.

15:32.540 --> 15:34.977
You and me.

15:35.021 --> 15:36.370
We're sisters.

15:36.413 --> 15:38.372
- Uh, no.
No.

15:38.415 --> 15:41.244
I am definitely a good witch.

15:41.288 --> 15:42.898
A--a Delilah.

15:42.942 --> 15:44.987
- No, sweetie,
you're not.

15:45.031 --> 15:47.555
That's why they kicked you
out of that group.

15:47.598 --> 15:50.384
That's why you're cursed.

15:50.427 --> 15:52.734
You're a Dark Witch.

15:52.777 --> 15:54.823
And cheers to that.

16:00.220 --> 16:01.221
- What's going on?

16:01.264 --> 16:02.744
- Madonna's a traitor.

16:02.787 --> 16:05.138
She's been working
for my father.

16:05.181 --> 16:06.574
- Our Madonna?

16:06.617 --> 16:09.403
- Yep, he hired her
to spy on me.

16:09.446 --> 16:11.448
She gave him my blood.

16:11.492 --> 16:12.972
- For what?

16:13.015 --> 16:14.582
- I don't know,

16:14.625 --> 16:17.019
but I'm gonna find out,
and when I do,

16:17.063 --> 16:18.499
I'm gonna kill him.

16:18.542 --> 16:20.022
I should have done it
a long time ago.

16:20.066 --> 16:21.719
- Wait, it could be
the human side of me talking,

16:21.763 --> 16:23.504
but maybe you should
cool off first.

16:23.547 --> 16:26.072
- Perhaps you should leech me?

16:26.115 --> 16:28.813
Oh, you can't anymore.

16:31.077 --> 16:32.774
- Olivia.

16:32.817 --> 16:35.429
- Sequoia was upset
about something,

16:35.472 --> 16:37.431
and she tried to leave town
but before she could,

16:37.474 --> 16:38.562
something killed her.

16:38.606 --> 16:39.824
Something she couldn't see.

16:39.868 --> 16:41.391
- Another killer ghost?

16:41.435 --> 16:43.393
- It seems like a ghost,
but it doesn't make any sense.

16:43.437 --> 16:45.265
Why frame it as a suicide?

16:45.308 --> 16:46.396
- Cover up a murder?

16:46.440 --> 16:48.094
- Which is not a ghostly MO.

16:48.137 --> 16:50.487
They like their presence
to be known.

16:50.531 --> 16:52.620
What's that for?

16:52.663 --> 16:54.187
- Becoming human gift
for Lem.

16:54.230 --> 16:56.885
Since he got himself healed,
we're down a fighter.

16:56.928 --> 16:58.974
Figured I'd give him a new way
to battle evil.

16:59.018 --> 17:02.499
- Something or someone
cut out Sequoia's tongue

17:02.543 --> 17:03.718
so she couldn't talk to me.

17:03.761 --> 17:04.980
And she didn't want Kai

17:05.024 --> 17:07.287
to know she was still around.

17:07.330 --> 17:08.766
What if Kai killed her?

17:08.810 --> 17:10.768
- It doesn't make sense.

17:10.812 --> 17:12.335
Kai is not invisible.

17:12.379 --> 17:13.815
[loud creak]

17:13.858 --> 17:15.338
- Did you hear that?

17:15.382 --> 17:17.427
- Yeah.

17:17.471 --> 17:18.689
- Someone's here.

17:18.733 --> 17:21.692
[suspenseful music]

17:21.736 --> 17:29.004
♪

17:29.874 --> 17:31.267
- That was not a ghost.

17:31.311 --> 17:35.837
♪

17:39.188 --> 17:41.538
[Bing Crosby's
"White Christmas"]

17:41.582 --> 17:47.414
- ♪ Of a white Christmas

17:47.457 --> 17:53.637
♪ Just like the ones
I used to know ♪

17:53.681 --> 17:55.683
- Does your father always
celebrate Christmas

17:55.726 --> 17:57.076
at this time of year?

17:57.119 --> 17:58.425
- [scoffs]

17:58.468 --> 18:01.863
- ♪ Where the treetops
glisten ♪

18:01.906 --> 18:06.389
♪ And children listen

18:06.433 --> 18:07.956
- What's wrong?
Who's that girl?

18:07.999 --> 18:09.218
- It's me.

18:09.262 --> 18:11.699
[dramatic music]

18:15.442 --> 18:15.659
.

18:15.703 --> 18:17.444
♪

18:17.487 --> 18:19.359
- What do you mean
that girl is you?

18:19.402 --> 18:22.101
- She looks exactly like me
when I was nine,

18:22.144 --> 18:25.104
the year my mom died
and everything went to hell.

18:25.147 --> 18:27.149
- This is weird, even for us.

18:27.193 --> 18:29.369
- Uh-huh.
- What do you wanna do?

18:29.412 --> 18:32.720
- ♪ Used to know

18:32.763 --> 18:34.200
- Help her.

18:34.243 --> 18:38.769
- ♪ Where the treetops
glisten ♪

18:38.813 --> 18:40.510
- Hi.

18:40.554 --> 18:42.643
- ♪ And children listen

18:42.686 --> 18:46.037
- [exhales deeply]

18:46.081 --> 18:47.256
Are you okay?

18:47.300 --> 18:49.606
- ♪ Sleigh bells in the snow

18:49.650 --> 18:52.261
- Is anyone hurting you?

18:52.305 --> 18:54.785
♪

18:54.829 --> 18:56.874
- Daddy.

18:56.918 --> 18:59.225
- ♪ Dreaming of a...

18:59.268 --> 19:02.228
[dramatic music swells]

19:02.271 --> 19:06.971
♪

19:07.015 --> 19:10.801
- Sweetheart, why don't you go
and get some Christmas cookies?

19:10.845 --> 19:15.197
♪

19:15.241 --> 19:17.199
Livy.

19:17.243 --> 19:18.853
It's so good to see you.

19:18.896 --> 19:20.071
- [grunts]

19:20.115 --> 19:22.900
Don't you dare call me that.

19:22.944 --> 19:26.165
And don't act like
this is normal.

19:26.208 --> 19:28.036
Like we're normal.

19:28.079 --> 19:30.169
You infiltrate my town.

19:30.212 --> 19:33.563
You hire someone to befriend me
and spy on me.

19:33.607 --> 19:35.261
You take my blood?

19:35.304 --> 19:37.176
- Livy, I can explain.

19:37.219 --> 19:40.091
- What the hell
is going on here?

19:40.135 --> 19:42.050
What is she?

19:42.093 --> 19:44.313
- Everything okay out there?

19:44.357 --> 19:47.490
- Philip, you didn't tell me
we were expecting guests.

19:47.534 --> 19:49.362
What a lovely surprise.

19:49.405 --> 19:51.233
[whispers]
- Mom.

19:51.277 --> 19:54.236
- I'm Jean Charity.

19:54.280 --> 19:56.934
- I'm Olivia.

19:56.978 --> 19:58.893
- That's my daughter's name.

19:58.936 --> 20:01.243
[peaceful music]

20:01.287 --> 20:03.071
- Who wants eggnog?

20:03.114 --> 20:06.292
♪

20:08.511 --> 20:12.341
- It's actually
an art installation.

20:12.385 --> 20:15.214
Yes, Midnight is the new Marfa.

20:15.257 --> 20:18.521
[laughs]
Enjoy.

20:19.653 --> 20:21.220
[sighs]

20:21.263 --> 20:23.134
This is such a nightmare.

20:23.178 --> 20:26.442
I'm still so shaken up
about Sequoia.

20:26.486 --> 20:29.793
How could I not see
that she needed help?

20:29.837 --> 20:32.013
- Don't blame yourself.

20:32.056 --> 20:35.016
[dramatic music]

20:35.059 --> 20:36.496
♪

20:36.539 --> 20:39.150
People have their secrets.

20:39.194 --> 20:42.328
- [breathing heavily]

20:42.371 --> 20:44.068
["Silent Night" playing]

20:44.112 --> 20:45.461
- Are they real?

20:45.505 --> 20:47.985
- They're living, breathing
manifestations

20:48.029 --> 20:50.031
created from my memory.

20:50.074 --> 20:53.600
♪

20:53.643 --> 20:55.297
You know, when I found out

20:55.341 --> 20:57.995
what your stepmother
and those men did to you,

20:58.039 --> 21:00.389
I was devastated.

21:00.433 --> 21:03.610
The guilt was overbearing.

21:03.653 --> 21:05.307
But by then, it was too late.

21:05.351 --> 21:07.048
You ran away, and you didn't
wanna have

21:07.091 --> 21:08.354
anything to do with me.

21:08.397 --> 21:10.399
- So you hired people
to spy on me.

21:10.443 --> 21:12.140
- I had all the money
in the world

21:12.183 --> 21:15.883
and anything that
I ever desired at my disposal

21:15.926 --> 21:19.016
except for the one thing
that I really wanted:

21:19.060 --> 21:21.018
you and your mother back.

21:21.062 --> 21:24.195
So I found another way:

21:24.239 --> 21:26.067
watching you in Midnight.

21:26.110 --> 21:28.025
I learned that magic was real,

21:28.069 --> 21:30.680
so I found a spell that
would make my wish come true.

21:30.724 --> 21:33.553
With your blood
and your mother's ashes,

21:33.596 --> 21:37.383
I was able to recreate this
one last happy memory,

21:37.426 --> 21:43.127
a magical diorama
of this one perfect moment.

21:43.171 --> 21:45.826
- You can't rewrite history.

21:45.869 --> 21:49.351
- Livy, I know that
I've made mistakes,

21:49.395 --> 21:51.875
but isn't this what
you've always wanted,

21:51.919 --> 21:54.225
to have all of us
back together again?

21:54.269 --> 21:57.228
[dramatic music]

21:57.272 --> 22:00.188
- Daddy, look what Mama got me.

22:00.231 --> 22:02.712
- Look at that.

22:02.756 --> 22:04.192
Ballet shoes.

22:04.235 --> 22:05.802
You gonna put 'em on?

22:05.846 --> 22:07.369
Okay, go ahead.

22:07.413 --> 22:09.719
["Silent Night" continues]

22:09.763 --> 22:11.852
- Livy, would you like
to help us open presents?

22:11.895 --> 22:18.946
- ♪ Christ our savior
is born ♪

22:20.426 --> 22:24.691
- Olivia, wait.

22:24.734 --> 22:26.170
- We should go.

22:26.214 --> 22:28.390
You came here to kill
your father,

22:28.434 --> 22:30.740
not drink eggnog with ghosts
of Christmas past.

22:30.784 --> 22:32.525
I'm worried you're
getting sucked in.

22:32.568 --> 22:34.744
- I know, it's warped.

22:34.788 --> 22:37.268
I just want to talk to my mom.

22:37.312 --> 22:39.619
Five minutes.

22:39.662 --> 22:46.321
- ♪ Shepherds quake
at the sight ♪

22:46.365 --> 22:47.931
- Kai's in a session.

22:47.975 --> 22:49.629
As long as you keep
an eye on him,

22:49.672 --> 22:50.934
he can't hurt anyone.

22:50.978 --> 22:52.806
I'm gonna check
out his office,

22:52.849 --> 22:54.982
see if I can find evidence
he killed Sequoia.

22:55.025 --> 22:56.679
- Be careful, Manfred.

22:56.723 --> 22:58.420
If you're right
and he can absorb powers,

22:58.464 --> 22:59.943
who knows what
he's capable of?

22:59.987 --> 23:02.946
[suspenseful music]

23:02.990 --> 23:09.997
♪

23:14.480 --> 23:16.090
[device beeps]

23:27.841 --> 23:29.495
[Patsy Cline's "Three
Cigarettes in an Ashtray"]

23:29.538 --> 23:32.149
- ♪ My love and I

23:32.193 --> 23:38.939
♪ in a small café

23:38.982 --> 23:43.552
♪ Then a stranger came along

23:43.596 --> 23:47.774
♪ And everything went wrong

23:47.817 --> 23:52.561
♪ Now there's
three cigarettes ♪

23:52.605 --> 23:58.611
♪ in the ashtray

23:58.654 --> 24:03.964
♪ I watched her
take him from me ♪

24:04.007 --> 24:05.922
- It wasn't Kai.

24:05.966 --> 24:07.489
- Yeah, duh.

24:07.533 --> 24:09.709
♪

24:09.752 --> 24:11.406
- Lyric, where are you?

24:11.450 --> 24:14.235
[thud]
[crashing]

24:14.278 --> 24:17.238
[dramatic music]

24:17.281 --> 24:19.893
[crashing]

24:19.936 --> 24:24.811
♪

24:24.854 --> 24:27.770
[crashing]

24:27.814 --> 24:29.685
I thought Sequoia
was like your sister?

24:29.729 --> 24:31.382
- And I thought she was
a true believer,

24:31.426 --> 24:33.254
but she was going
to betray Kai.

24:33.297 --> 24:34.473
♪

24:34.516 --> 24:36.083
- Sequoia was afraid of Kai.

24:36.126 --> 24:37.519
Why aren't you?

24:37.563 --> 24:39.216
- Kai said he's not
going to hurt anyone,

24:39.260 --> 24:40.522
so I had to protect him.

24:40.566 --> 24:42.089
- [grunts]

24:42.132 --> 24:44.004
[groaning]

24:44.047 --> 24:46.354
- And I know you're
screwing his wife!

24:46.397 --> 24:48.399
- [choking]

24:48.443 --> 24:51.098
[groaning]

24:51.141 --> 24:58.192
♪

24:59.498 --> 25:01.064
- [screams]

25:01.108 --> 25:03.414
- [gasping]

25:03.458 --> 25:06.679
♪

25:10.683 --> 25:11.074
.

25:11.118 --> 25:12.728
- That's right, dear,

25:12.772 --> 25:15.644
drown the sadness
in chardonnay.

25:15.688 --> 25:17.080
- More.

25:17.124 --> 25:18.473
I don't get it.

25:18.517 --> 25:21.084
I don't understand how I
could be a Dark Witch.

25:21.128 --> 25:24.131
I have always practiced magic
with good intentions.

25:24.174 --> 25:27.003
- Well, good intentions
only get in the way, dear.

25:27.047 --> 25:28.527
Wait till you see
what you can do

25:28.570 --> 25:30.703
when you stop worrying
about the consequences.

25:30.746 --> 25:32.182
- Consequences?

25:32.226 --> 25:35.446
That's just a nice word for
"people getting hurt."

25:35.490 --> 25:36.752
- Hmm.

25:36.796 --> 25:38.275
I was like you once,

25:38.319 --> 25:41.104
afraid of what I was
truly capable of.

25:41.148 --> 25:42.932
I know you can feel it,

25:42.976 --> 25:44.891
all that untapped power.

25:44.934 --> 25:47.241
But to become your full self,

25:47.284 --> 25:50.070
you have to let go
of your fears,

25:50.113 --> 25:52.159
embrace the Darkness.

25:52.202 --> 25:55.597
- I'm a powerful witch
the way that I am.

25:55.641 --> 25:59.688
- Well, your furry little
friend here says otherwise.

25:59.732 --> 26:01.037
[laughs]

26:01.081 --> 26:03.431
But you can change that.

26:03.474 --> 26:05.041
- You know how to break
the curse?

26:05.085 --> 26:06.521
- Of course I do.

26:06.565 --> 26:07.783
That's why I'm here.

26:07.827 --> 26:09.480
Just pledge yourself
to the Darkness,

26:09.524 --> 26:12.353
officially join your Brothers
and Sisters of Theophilus,

26:12.396 --> 26:14.094
and then your lover here
will be saved.

26:14.137 --> 26:15.312
Now, doesn't that
sounds fabulous?

26:15.356 --> 26:16.966
- No, it does not
sound fabulous.

26:17.010 --> 26:20.579
I could never pledge myself
to the Darkness.

26:20.622 --> 26:23.103
- Well, if you're not
willing to do what it takes,

26:23.146 --> 26:25.671
then you can
kiss him good-bye.

26:25.714 --> 26:27.498
Is that what you want?

26:28.282 --> 26:30.589
- I just want the man
that I love back.

26:31.938 --> 26:34.244
- [sighs]

26:36.507 --> 26:37.639
- [gasps]

26:37.683 --> 26:38.640
- Ooh.

26:38.684 --> 26:40.163
- [gasps]
The curse.

26:40.207 --> 26:42.122
- Don't worry, he's in
a protective cloaking spell.

26:42.165 --> 26:44.167
Dark Magic, of course.

26:44.211 --> 26:46.692
He'll be safe for 48 hours.

26:46.735 --> 26:47.954
Consider it a freebie.

26:47.997 --> 26:50.478
But you have a decision
to make:

26:50.521 --> 26:53.960
either let the curse run
its course, or--

26:54.003 --> 26:55.614
- Embrace the Darkness.

26:55.657 --> 26:57.006
- That's right.

26:57.050 --> 26:58.312
♪

26:58.355 --> 27:00.140
Call me when you're ready.

27:00.183 --> 27:07.408
♪

27:10.846 --> 27:12.892
- She's amazing, isn't she?

27:12.935 --> 27:16.156
- Well, she has a great mother.

27:16.199 --> 27:17.461
[acoustic
"Away in a Manger"]

27:17.505 --> 27:20.682
My mom died when I was young.

27:20.726 --> 27:24.164
Sometimes I wonder...

27:24.207 --> 27:27.210
if she'd be disappointed
in who I am now.

27:27.254 --> 27:30.170
I don't think I became
the person

27:30.213 --> 27:31.998
she wanted me to be.

27:32.041 --> 27:34.522
- When I first had my daughter,

27:34.565 --> 27:38.004
I wanted her
to play the violin,

27:38.047 --> 27:40.833
like I did as a girl.

27:40.876 --> 27:43.836
But she hated it.

27:43.879 --> 27:45.707
♪

27:45.751 --> 27:49.450
Then she found ballet.

27:49.493 --> 27:54.281
And she's absolutely
breathtaking.

27:54.324 --> 27:56.370
What I'm trying to say is that

27:56.413 --> 28:00.026
she isn't who I'd hoped
she'd be.

28:00.069 --> 28:03.986
She's so much better
than I imagined.

28:04.030 --> 28:08.774
♪

28:08.817 --> 28:10.601
- Daddy?
- Yep.

28:10.645 --> 28:13.082
I don't feel good.

28:13.126 --> 28:15.041
[suspenseful music]

28:15.084 --> 28:16.477
- Oh, honey.

28:16.520 --> 28:20.394
I think you just had too many
gingerbread cookies.

28:20.437 --> 28:22.396
You keep decorating that cake,

28:22.439 --> 28:24.920
and Daddy will be
right back, okay?

28:24.964 --> 28:26.052
Okay.

28:26.095 --> 28:33.363
♪

28:43.809 --> 28:45.898
Blood for my daughter,

28:45.941 --> 28:49.902
blood for my wife,

28:49.945 --> 28:52.600
to keep the memory alive.

28:52.643 --> 28:59.650
♪

29:02.653 --> 29:07.180
- I wish
this could be real.

29:07.223 --> 29:10.531
- Let's go.

29:12.141 --> 29:14.448
- Olivia.

29:14.491 --> 29:16.929
While meeting your family
has been wonderful,

29:16.972 --> 29:18.757
it's time to go.

29:18.800 --> 29:22.499
Your father just fed
his blood to...

29:22.543 --> 29:25.459
Olivia?

29:25.502 --> 29:27.461
Are you all right?

29:27.504 --> 29:29.158
- Yeah.

29:29.202 --> 29:30.420
I can't go.

29:30.464 --> 29:31.639
[dramatic music]

29:31.682 --> 29:32.988
It's Christmas.

29:33.032 --> 29:38.559
♪

29:39.516 --> 29:42.955
- So I'm safe for another
48 hours?

29:42.998 --> 29:45.044
- 46 1/2.

29:45.087 --> 29:48.047
[cell phone buzzing]

29:48.090 --> 29:49.439
Oh.

29:50.876 --> 29:51.964
Lem?

29:52.007 --> 29:53.530
- Feej, we've got a problem.

29:53.574 --> 29:55.619
Olivia and I went to confront
her father,

29:55.663 --> 29:57.621
who turns out,
is living in a memory

29:57.665 --> 29:59.188
he recreated with Dark Magic,

29:59.232 --> 30:01.321
and Olivia's fallen under
the spell.

30:01.364 --> 30:04.150
- Oh, my Goddess,
the one day you're human.

30:04.193 --> 30:05.629
- Don't remind me.

30:05.673 --> 30:07.153
I think her father's
trying to--

30:07.196 --> 30:08.981
[grunts]

30:09.024 --> 30:11.244
- Sorry, Lem,

30:11.287 --> 30:13.768
but no one's going
to ruin my Christmas.

30:18.991 --> 30:19.208
.

30:19.252 --> 30:21.297
- [gasps]

30:21.341 --> 30:24.300
[dramatic music]

30:24.344 --> 30:25.606
♪

30:25.649 --> 30:27.695
- What did you do to her?

30:27.738 --> 30:30.132
- He was investigating
Sequoia's murder.

30:30.176 --> 30:31.264
- Her murder?

30:31.307 --> 30:32.874
Sequoia killed herself.

30:32.918 --> 30:34.180
- No, she didn't.

30:34.223 --> 30:35.790
♪

30:35.834 --> 30:39.185
I was finally able
to contact Sequoia's ghost.

30:39.228 --> 30:40.882
She led me to Lyric,

30:40.926 --> 30:42.405
Who confessed to killing her

30:42.449 --> 30:43.798
before she tried
to kill me too.

30:43.842 --> 30:45.800
- Why would she do something
so awful?

30:45.844 --> 30:48.150
- She said she was trying
to protect you, Kai.

30:48.194 --> 30:49.891
♪

30:49.935 --> 30:51.197
Why would she say that?

30:51.240 --> 30:52.720
- I don't know.

30:52.763 --> 30:56.202
♪

31:04.297 --> 31:07.953
- Olivia, you can break
this spell.

31:07.996 --> 31:09.693
You just have to want to.

31:09.737 --> 31:13.915
♪

31:13.959 --> 31:16.265
- You know, never
in my wildest dreams

31:16.309 --> 31:19.834
did I ever imagine that
I'd have my daughter back.

31:19.878 --> 31:22.750
♪

31:22.793 --> 31:24.621
- You can have your fantasy,

31:24.665 --> 31:26.928
but let Olivia go.

31:26.972 --> 31:29.757
- I'm afraid I can't do that.

31:29.800 --> 31:31.977
I never planned
it to happen,

31:32.020 --> 31:33.848
but she's under
the spell now.

31:33.892 --> 31:35.981
If I end it,
they'll all go away,

31:36.024 --> 31:39.332
and I have no intention
of letting them go again.

31:39.375 --> 31:42.813
I finally have a chance
to right all my wrongs,

31:42.857 --> 31:44.772
to change the past.

31:44.815 --> 31:48.515
And...

31:48.558 --> 31:52.867
If you try anything,

31:52.911 --> 31:55.348
anything at all,

31:55.391 --> 31:59.178
I will kill you.

32:01.223 --> 32:02.572
How 'bout a Christmas carol?

32:02.616 --> 32:04.357
- Oh, yes.

32:04.400 --> 32:05.358
- "Jingle Bells"?

32:05.401 --> 32:06.881
- Mm-hmm.

32:06.925 --> 32:09.101
- ♪ Dun-dun-dun-dashing
through the snow ♪

32:09.144 --> 32:11.712
all: ♪ In a one-horse
open sleigh ♪

32:11.755 --> 32:13.975
♪ O'er the fields we go

32:14.019 --> 32:15.585
♪ Laughing all the way

32:15.629 --> 32:16.717
♪ Ha, ha, ha

32:16.760 --> 32:19.720
[dramatic music]

32:19.763 --> 32:23.202
♪

32:23.245 --> 32:24.638
- Madonna?

32:24.681 --> 32:26.640
M-Madonna.

32:26.683 --> 32:27.684
Are you okay?

32:27.728 --> 32:28.816
- Yeah.

32:28.859 --> 32:30.861
- What the hell happened
in here?

32:30.905 --> 32:32.428
- It's a long story.

32:32.472 --> 32:33.908
- We're looking for
Lem and Olivia.

32:33.952 --> 32:35.779
They went to go confront
her father,

32:35.823 --> 32:37.781
and now they're in trouble.

32:37.825 --> 32:39.914
- What kind of trouble?
- Dark Magic.

32:39.958 --> 32:42.134
I think Olivia's father
made a Mirage Enchantment.

32:42.177 --> 32:45.050
It allows you to recreate
the memory of a loved one.

32:45.093 --> 32:48.053
I think that I have a spell
that can reverse it.

32:48.096 --> 32:51.317
- But Olivia fell under
the spell, and if we don't

32:51.360 --> 32:54.537
stop it, she could be trapped
there forever.

32:54.581 --> 32:56.713
- Follow me.

32:56.757 --> 32:58.367
I know where they are.

32:58.411 --> 32:59.368
[doorbell rings]

32:59.412 --> 33:01.762
♪

33:01.805 --> 33:04.025
- Hi.
- Merry Christmas.

33:04.069 --> 33:06.027
- Oh.
[grunts]

33:06.071 --> 33:09.422
What the hell is going on here?

33:09.465 --> 33:11.250
[exciting music]

33:11.293 --> 33:12.773
[grunting]

33:12.816 --> 33:17.647
♪

33:17.691 --> 33:19.867
- Ho, ho, ho.

33:19.910 --> 33:21.869
- Madonna, thank goodness.

33:21.912 --> 33:23.088
- Oh.

33:23.131 --> 33:24.915
- Can you take this thing
off me?

33:24.959 --> 33:27.309
- Yes, I'm gonna
get you out of here.

33:27.353 --> 33:28.397
♪

33:28.441 --> 33:30.225
- Olivia's still under
the spell.

33:30.269 --> 33:32.097
- Fiji's working on that.

33:32.140 --> 33:34.360
You okay?
- Thank you.

33:37.319 --> 33:38.581
- Who wants dessert?

33:38.625 --> 33:45.849
♪

33:49.592 --> 33:51.464
- [grunting]

33:51.507 --> 33:52.465
♪

33:52.508 --> 33:57.818
- Memories belong...

33:57.861 --> 34:00.342
- No!

34:02.344 --> 34:04.825
[dramatic music]

34:04.868 --> 34:07.175
Blood for blood.

34:09.612 --> 34:11.310
- Olivia, stop.

34:11.353 --> 34:14.835
- Mmm.
- Listen to me.

34:14.878 --> 34:16.576
When I first leeched you,

34:16.619 --> 34:19.318
I had never felt so much
pain inside someone,

34:19.361 --> 34:23.539
and I told myself
I would do anything

34:23.583 --> 34:26.194
to make that pain go away.

34:26.238 --> 34:30.024
Vampire, human,
I'm your family,

34:30.068 --> 34:31.634
not this delusion.

34:31.678 --> 34:34.115
- You don't understand.

34:34.159 --> 34:36.074
I'm finally where I belong.

34:36.117 --> 34:38.902
♪

34:38.946 --> 34:41.427
- Blood for blood.

34:41.470 --> 34:43.342
Flame for flame.

34:43.385 --> 34:46.040
♪

34:46.084 --> 34:47.607
- [groans]

34:47.650 --> 34:48.869
- How much longer, Feej?

34:48.912 --> 34:51.132
- My Light Magic,

34:51.176 --> 34:53.395
it's not strong enough.

34:53.439 --> 34:55.963
- I know Celeste
got in your head.

34:56.006 --> 34:58.008
But remember who you are.

34:58.052 --> 34:59.358
You're Fiji Cavanaugh.

34:59.401 --> 35:01.838
- What if that's not enough?

35:01.882 --> 35:03.710
I have to embrace the Darkness.

35:03.753 --> 35:07.061
[breathing heavily]

35:07.105 --> 35:11.544
♪

35:11.587 --> 35:13.067
[screaming]

35:13.111 --> 35:14.547
[gasps]

35:23.686 --> 35:23.904
.

35:23.947 --> 35:26.385
- [breathing heavily]

35:26.428 --> 35:28.169
[dramatic music]

35:28.213 --> 35:30.084
- [gasps]

35:34.219 --> 35:36.134
What happened to me?

35:37.744 --> 35:39.180
[gasps]

35:39.224 --> 35:41.704
What the hell am I wearing?

35:41.748 --> 35:43.706
- [laughs]
Come here.

35:43.750 --> 35:46.144
- [sighs]
- You're okay.

35:46.187 --> 35:48.146
- [moans]

35:48.189 --> 35:53.673
♪

35:57.024 --> 35:59.592
No, I'm not.

36:02.203 --> 36:03.726
- Go.

36:03.770 --> 36:06.425
- Thank you.
- Yeah.

36:09.428 --> 36:11.430
- Daddy!

36:11.473 --> 36:14.172
- No,
I can't lose you.

36:19.438 --> 36:20.917
- [gasping]

36:20.961 --> 36:24.747
[panting]
That felt good.

36:24.791 --> 36:27.489
- Let me see your hands.

36:36.890 --> 36:39.153
- [crying]

36:40.720 --> 36:43.157
[solemn music]

36:43.201 --> 36:47.161
If you could be a father
to a fake daughter,

36:47.205 --> 36:51.905
why couldn't you be
a father to me?

36:51.948 --> 36:54.821
- When your mother died,
I was broken.

36:54.864 --> 36:57.389
- [scoffs]
- I couldn't be a good father.

36:57.432 --> 36:59.304
- I needed you to protect me.

36:59.347 --> 37:01.044
I need you to tell me

37:01.088 --> 37:03.264
everything was
gonna be okay.

37:03.308 --> 37:05.179
- I can be there for you now.

37:05.223 --> 37:08.269
- No.
- Livy, please stay with me.

37:08.313 --> 37:10.010
All we have is each other.

37:10.053 --> 37:14.057
- My entire life,
I have let anger and pain

37:14.101 --> 37:18.279
protect me because I never
wanted to feel as alone

37:18.323 --> 37:20.803
in this world as
you made me feel.

37:20.847 --> 37:23.066
You!

37:23.110 --> 37:25.982
But I have to let go

37:26.026 --> 37:28.507
because I'm...

37:28.550 --> 37:32.119
I'm not alone anymore.

37:47.395 --> 37:49.789
- Why don't you just kill me?

37:49.832 --> 37:52.618
That's why you
came here, right,

37:52.661 --> 37:57.057
to put me out of my misery?

37:57.100 --> 38:01.322
Please.

38:01.366 --> 38:02.758
- No.

38:02.802 --> 38:10.070
♪

38:11.419 --> 38:14.204
I'm just gonna
return the favor.

38:14.248 --> 38:21.299
♪

38:48.108 --> 38:51.241
I can't believe I got sucked
into my dad's spell.

38:51.285 --> 38:54.636
- Family can have that
kind of hold on you.

38:55.942 --> 38:57.552
- Mm-hmm.

38:57.596 --> 39:00.903
For a long time,
I couldn't see myself

39:00.947 --> 39:03.558
any other way than broken.

39:03.602 --> 39:06.344
But...

39:07.954 --> 39:10.783
But the past is the past.

39:12.915 --> 39:15.744
- Well, I love you,

39:15.788 --> 39:20.183
past, present, and future.

39:21.794 --> 39:24.710
- And I love you.

39:26.233 --> 39:29.279
Vampire....human.

39:29.323 --> 39:31.194
- [laughs]

39:33.588 --> 39:35.416
- You're my family now.

39:35.460 --> 39:37.810
- [laughs]

39:43.337 --> 39:47.254
- Do you feel different?

39:50.431 --> 39:52.607
- Well, I don't feel evil,

39:52.651 --> 39:54.566
if that's what
you're asking.

39:54.609 --> 39:57.830
[solemn music]

39:58.483 --> 40:00.441
- Mm.

40:00.485 --> 40:02.922
♪

40:02.965 --> 40:05.968
I'm still afraid
of it, but...

40:06.012 --> 40:08.928
Dark Magic saved
Lem and Olivia tonight.

40:08.971 --> 40:11.583
Maybe it could save us too.

40:11.626 --> 40:13.802
- That was an emergency.

40:13.846 --> 40:15.804
- And this isn't?

40:15.848 --> 40:18.720
If you were in my shoes,
you wouldn't hesitate

40:18.764 --> 40:24.247
to do whatever it takes
to save me.

40:24.291 --> 40:26.554
Bobo...

40:26.598 --> 40:30.166
You are my family.

40:30.210 --> 40:33.300
Let me save you.

40:33.343 --> 40:36.259
- I don't want you to change
who you are for me.

40:36.303 --> 40:37.826
- And I won't.

40:37.870 --> 40:40.350
But I am done being afraid.

40:40.394 --> 40:42.265
I'm taking control now.

40:45.617 --> 40:47.923
All right.

40:50.143 --> 40:51.274
[laughs]

40:51.318 --> 40:55.235
♪

41:00.893 --> 41:02.503
- I found this in Lyric's room.

41:02.547 --> 41:06.159
Lyric didn't always have
the power to become invisible.

41:06.202 --> 41:09.684
She drank this,
and it gave her that power.

41:09.728 --> 41:11.860
- That iridescent glow.

41:11.904 --> 41:12.992
- It's monster energy.

41:13.035 --> 41:15.995
[ominous music]

41:16.038 --> 41:18.040
Sequoia discovered
Kai's secret.

41:18.084 --> 41:19.955
That's what she was
trying to tell me.

41:19.999 --> 41:22.828
- What kind of secret would
be worth killing somebody over?

41:22.871 --> 41:24.743
- I think I know
how to find out.

41:24.786 --> 41:29.530
♪

41:29.574 --> 41:32.838
[buttons clicking]

41:34.317 --> 41:37.364
[jukebox whirring]

41:43.152 --> 41:46.329
[Patsy Cline's "Three
Cigarettes in an Ashtray"]

41:46.373 --> 41:52.074
♪

41:52.118 --> 41:56.035
- ♪ Two cigarettes

41:56.078 --> 41:59.560
♪ In an ashtray

41:59.604 --> 42:00.561
♪

42:00.605 --> 42:03.216
♪ My love and I

42:03.259 --> 42:07.394
♪ In a small café

42:07.437 --> 42:10.571
♪

42:10.615 --> 42:15.141
♪ Then a stranger
came along ♪

42:15.184 --> 42:18.840
♪ And everything went wrong
